description: From Middle English untame, ontame, equivalent to un- (“not”) +‎ tame.

adjectives.description: untame (comparative more untame, superlative most untame)

description: From Middle English untamen, *untemien (attested as untemed), equivalent to un- (“back; reverse”) +‎ tame.

verbs.description: untame (third-person singular simple present untames, present participle untaming, simple past and past participle untamed)
